race.comment: Open race. Watch the market with PENTLE BAY (4) who is off 16 months over from England. Now with C Maher, he won at Leicester on debut before tackling a top 2yo Listed race, finishing second, beaten a whopping nine lengths by Bedtime Story, who was one of the best juveniles in the land at the time. The betting holds the key. AHHA AHHA (10) resumes. She did some good things over the Winter in 3yo company with the win two back rating highly. Should hold some residual fitness and the middle draws looks suitable. FEAR NO EVIL (2) resumes with a nice profile. He'll roll forward with Nash Rawiller on and can win fresh off some encouraging trial form. KHADIME (15) was much better second up and now looks ready to win.
